# Python test environment

Develop and run checks in **Docker** so your laptop does not need a local Python
toolchain for the default workflow. The image ships **Python 3.12**, **Ruff**,
and **pytest**; your code lives under [`src/`](src/) (sample package **`sample`**)
and [`tests/`](tests/).

---

## Layout

| Path | Role |
| --- | --- |
| [`run.sh`](run.sh) | Entrypoint: `docker compose … run --rm dev …`. Supports `--rebuild`, `--shell`. |
| [`justfile`](justfile) | Shortcuts: `just lint`, `just test`, `just ci`, … |
| [`docker/Dockerfile`](docker/Dockerfile) | `python:3.12-slim-bookworm`, `pip install -e ".[dev]"` |
| [`docker/docker-compose.yml`](docker/docker-compose.yml) | Mounts `..` → `/python` (rw) |
| [`pyproject.toml`](pyproject.toml) | Package metadata, Ruff/pytest settings, optional **`dev`** extras |
| [`.devcontainer/`](.devcontainer/) | Dev container (same stack as the runner) |
| [`.editorconfig`](.editorconfig) | Editor defaults (4-space indents for Python) |

---

## Prerequisites

- [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/) with **Compose v2**
- Optional: [`just`](https://github.com/casey/just) for [`justfile`](justfile) tasks

---

## Quick start

From **`test-env/python`**:

```bash
./run.sh                    # default: pytest -q
./run.sh ruff check .
./run.sh ruff format --check .
./run.sh pytest -q
./run.sh --rebuild          # after pyproject.toml or Dockerfile edits
./run.sh --shell            # bash inside the runner
```

With **`just`**:

```bash
just              # list recipes
just lint         # ruff check
just fix          # ruff check --fix
just format-check # ruff format --check
just format       # ruff format
just test         # pytest
just ci           # lint + format-check + test
just shell        # interactive shell
```

After changing **dependencies** in `pyproject.toml`, run **`./run.sh --rebuild`**
(or `just rebuild`) so the image picks them up.

---

## CI

[`.github/workflows/python.yml`](../../.github/workflows/python.yml) runs Ruff
and pytest when files under `test-env/python/**` change.
